  <h2>Signs your home needs duct cleaning now</h2>
  <p>You usually do not need a test to know, the signs are visible and in the air:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dust returns fast,</strong> discharging from registers within hours of cleaning floors.</li>
    <li><strong>A musty or stale odor</strong> when the AC first kicks on.</li>
    <li><strong>Indoor-only allergies,</strong> worse inside than outdoors.</li>
    <li><strong>Recent renovation, drywall, or construction dust.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Evidence of rodents,</strong> droppings or chewed insulation.</li>
    <li><strong>A past water-damage or HVAC-flooding event.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Visible pet-dander buildup</strong> in the return grilles.</li>
    <li><strong>An air handler over 10 years old</strong> that has never been cleaned.</li>
  </ul>

