  <h2>When duct cleaning is not the answer</h2>
  <p>Cleaning is not a cure-all, and we lose sales saying so. If your main complaint is one of these, the money belongs elsewhere:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Humidity or clammy air:</strong> usually a sizing or equipment issue better solved by a <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">tune-up</a> or <a href="/services/ac-replacement-tampa/">right-sized replacement</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Uneven room temperatures:</strong> typically a duct-sealing or airflow problem, not a dirt problem.</li>
    <li><strong>High bills with weak cooling:</strong> often a charge or coil issue our <a href="/services/ac-repair-tampa/">AC repair</a> team diagnoses first.</li>
    <li><strong>Allergy control as the real goal:</strong> filtration and purifiers under <a href="/services/indoor-air-quality-tampa/">indoor air quality</a> outperform cleaning alone.</li>
  </ul>

  <OwnerTip>
    <p>"Be careful with the $99 duct-cleaning coupons. Nine times out of ten that crew vacuums the first few feet, sprays a deodorizer, and leaves the biofilm on the coil untouched, which is the part that actually smells. A real cleaning puts the system under containment and scrubs the whole run. Ask to see the before-and-after camera footage. If we clean your ducts, you get it, the same honesty we bring to a <a href="/services/heat-pump-repair-tampa/">heat pump</a> or AC call."</p>
  </OwnerTip>

  <h2>Keeping ducts clean after the service</h2>
  <p>A cleaning resets the system, but the right habits keep it clean for years:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Run the right filter:</strong> a MERV 8 to 11 pleated filter for most Tampa homes, changed every 60 to 90 days.</li>
    <li><strong>Do not over-MERV an undersized return,</strong> since a too-restrictive filter freezes coils and burns out blowers.</li>
    <li><strong>Pair it with a coil and drain service</strong> on your regular <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">maintenance</a> visit.</li>
    <li><strong>Consider a controller</strong> with a filter reminder, easy to add during a <a href="/services/thermostat-installation-tampa/">thermostat install</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cleaning vs. sealing: they are not the same job</h2>
  <p>Homeowners often ask for "duct cleaning" when the real fix is "duct sealing," and they solve different problems:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Duct cleaning</strong> removes dust, dander, mold, and debris from inside the ducts. It fixes dirty air and odors.</li>
    <li><strong>Duct sealing</strong> closes leaks at joints and the air handler. It fixes high bills, uneven rooms, and humid air pulled in from the attic.</li>
    <li><strong>Many homes need both,</strong> and we measure with a duct-blaster test before recommending either, so you do not pay for the wrong one.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If your home has no ductwork at all, like many ductless setups, cleaning is moot, and a <a href="/services/mini-split-installation-tampa/">mini-split</a> sidesteps the issue entirely. Bigger sealing-plus-cleaning projects qualify for <a href="/financing/">0% financing</a> so the right fix is affordable.</p>

  <h2>What we pull out of Tampa Bay ducts</h2>
  <p>The before-and-after camera footage tells the story, but here is what is typically hiding in a 10-year-uncleaned Florida system:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Compacted dust and pet dander</strong> lining the supply trunks.</li>
    <li><strong>Pollen packed into returns</strong> from years of spring blooms in <a href="/service-areas/lutz-home-air-conditioning-service/">Lutz</a> and the tree-heavy suburbs.</li>
    <li><strong>Biofilm and mold</strong> on the coil and the first few feet of supply, the source of that musty smell.</li>
    <li><strong>Construction debris</strong> in homes that were never cleaned after the build.</li>
  </ul>

